spec: struct_extra107
version: ">=3.9"
backend: python_module(struct)

docs: https://docs.python.org/3/library/struct.html

provenance:
  derived_from:
    - "https://docs.python.org/3/library/struct.html — Python struct module documentation"
    - "Test vectors verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10"
  not_derived_from:
    - "CPython source: Modules/_struct.c"
    - "CPython source: Lib/struct.py"
    - "struct_extra106.zspec.zsdl — covers struct.Struct class-level method qualnames (pack, unpack, pack_into, unpack_from, iter_unpack) as equality checks / Struct.__init__ is wrapper_descriptor / all five methods are method_descriptor (table + invariants)."
    - "struct_extra105.zspec.zsdl — covers struct.__spec__ attributes (name, __class__.__name__) / struct.__name__ and __package__ equality and lengths / struct.error method qualnames (__init__=BaseException.__init__, __str__=BaseException.__str__) and init type (wrapper_descriptor) (table + invariants)."
    - "struct_extra104.zspec.zsdl — covers Struct.size/format getset_descriptor qualnames and __objclass__ / module-level function qualname equality for all six functions / iter_unpack qualname and function module equality (table + invariants)."
    - "struct_extra103.zspec.zsdl — covers calcsize for compound format strings / repeat-count formats / fixed-size string formats / struct module attribute checks (table + invariants)."
    - "struct_extra102.zspec.zsdl — covers calcsize for single-char format codes and two-element composites (table + invariants)."
    - "struct_extra101.zspec.zsdl — covers struct.error class identity (__name__/__module__/__bases__[0].__name__/__mro__.__len__()==4/__class__.__name__=='type') / Struct class attribute equality / Struct method types and instance size (table + invariants)."
    - "struct_extra100.zspec.zsdl — covers Struct instance method qualname lengths / module-level function qualname lengths / Struct class-level method_descriptor type names (table + invariants)."
    - "struct_extra99.zspec.zsdl — covers module-level function __doc__ lengths / Struct.size/__format__ __doc__ equality and lengths (table + invariants)."
    - "struct_extra98.zspec.zsdl — covers Struct.size/__format__ getset_descriptor class names and qualnames (table + invariants)."
    - "struct_extra95.zspec.zsdl — covers pack_into/unpack_from/iter_unpack __qualname__.__len__() / Struct.__qualname__.__len__()==6 / error.__qualname__.__len__()==5 / module-level function __module__.__eq__('_struct') (table + invariants)."
  notes:
    - "This spec extends struct through struct_extra106; it does NOT duplicate invariants present in those files."
    - "Wave 271 theme: struct.Struct.size and struct.Struct.format are getset_descriptors — their __qualname__ strings are 'Struct.size' (11 chars) and 'Struct.format' (13 chars); both have __objclass__.__name__=='Struct'; their type is getset_descriptor; module-level calcsize/pack/unpack have qualname string equality; struct.Struct.__doc__ is a str."
    - "struct.Struct.size.__qualname__ == 'Struct.size'. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "struct.Struct.format.__qualname__ == 'Struct.format'. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "struct.Struct.size.__objclass__.__name__ == 'Struct'. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "struct.Struct.format.__objclass__.__name__ == 'Struct'. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "len('Struct.size') == 11 ('Struct.'=7 + 'size'=4). Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "len('Struct.format') == 13 ('Struct.'=7 + 'format'=6). Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "struct.Struct.size.__qualname__.__eq__('Struct.size') == True. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "struct.Struct.format.__qualname__.__eq__('Struct.format') == True. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "type(struct.Struct.size).__name__ == 'getset_descriptor'. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "type(struct.Struct.format).__name__ == 'getset_descriptor'. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "struct.Struct.__doc__.__class__.__name__ == 'str'. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "struct.calcsize.__qualname__.__eq__('calcsize') == True. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "struct.pack.__qualname__.__eq__('pack') == True. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "struct.unpack.__qualname__.__eq__('unpack') == True. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "Note: struct.Struct.size and struct.Struct.format are C-level getset_descriptor objects (defined in Modules/_struct.c). struct_extra98 anchors their class names and qualnames at a high level; struct_extra104 anchors their __objclass__ equality; this spec anchors the qualname string equality as equality checks (__eq__) and __objclass__.__name__ equality in a new grouped table focused on the 'Struct.attr' qualname pattern."
    - "Note: struct.calcsize, struct.pack, struct.unpack are C-level builtin_function_or_method objects (from _struct). Their qualnames are 'calcsize', 'pack', 'unpack' (no 'Struct.' prefix) because they are module-level functions, not class methods. struct_extra104 anchors these qualname equalities; this spec anchors them in a grouped table alongside the Struct.size/format descriptor qualnames."
    - "Note: struct_extra105 anchors struct.__name__ and struct.__package__ equality/lengths; this spec anchors the related Struct class-level descriptor qualnames as eq checks in the context of the 'Struct.attr' qualname pattern, complementing struct_extra98 and struct_extra104."
    - "All expected values verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
  created_at: "2026-04-10T00:00:00Z"

error_model: python_exceptions

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# struct.Struct.size.__qualname__.__eq__('Struct.size')
# struct.Struct.format.__qualname__.__eq__('Struct.format')
# struct.Struct.size.__objclass__.__name__.__eq__('Struct')
# struct.Struct.format.__objclass__.__name__.__eq__('Struct')
# len(struct.Struct.size.__qualname__) == 11
#
# Wave 271 theme: Struct.size and Struct.format qualname string equality and __objclass__.
#
# struct.Struct.size and struct.Struct.format are getset_descriptor objects at
# the class level. Their qualnames are 'Struct.size' (11 chars: 'Struct.'=7 +
# 'size'=4) and 'Struct.format' (13 chars: 'Struct.'=7 + 'format'=6). Both
# have __objclass__.__name__=='Struct'. struct_extra98 anchors class names and
# qualnames (via __class__.__name__ and __qualname__ as attributes); struct_extra104
# anchors the __objclass__ for these; this spec anchors the qualname __eq__()
# method call and __objclass__.__name__ as a grouped equality table.
# Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

table struct_extra107.Struct_size_and_format_qualname_eq_and_objclass:
  description: "Struct.size.__qualname__.__eq__('Struct.size')==True / Struct.format.__qualname__.__eq__('Struct.format')==True / Struct.size.__objclass__.__name__.__eq__('Struct')==True / Struct.format.__objclass__.__name__.__eq__('Struct')==True / Struct.size.__qualname__.__len__()==11 — size qualname is 'Struct.size' (11 chars; 'Struct.'=7+'size'=4); format qualname is 'Struct.format' (13 chars; 'Struct.'=7+'format'=6); both __objclass__ are Struct; extra98 anchors qualnames; extra104 anchors __objclass__; first structattr107 anchor"
  kind: python_call_eq
  category: descriptor_identity
  id_prefix: structattr107

  columns: [id, function, args, expected, description]
  rows:
    - [size_qualname_eq,      "Struct.size.__qualname__.__eq__",           ["Struct.size"],   true, "Struct.size.__qualname__ is 'Struct.size' (11 chars; 'Struct.'=7 + 'size'=4; getset_descriptor in _struct.c)"]
    - [format_qualname_eq,    "Struct.format.__qualname__.__eq__",         ["Struct.format"], true, "Struct.format.__qualname__ is 'Struct.format' (13 chars; 'Struct.'=7 + 'format'=6; getset_descriptor in _struct.c)"]
    - [size_objclass_eq,      "Struct.size.__objclass__.__name__.__eq__",  ["Struct"],        true, "Struct.size.__objclass__.__name__ is 'Struct' (__objclass__ is the class the descriptor is defined on)"]
    - [format_objclass_eq,    "Struct.format.__objclass__.__name__.__eq__", ["Struct"],       true, "Struct.format.__objclass__.__name__ is 'Struct' (same __objclass__ for both size and format descriptors)"]
    - [size_qualname_len,     "Struct.size.__qualname__.__len__",          [],                11,   "Struct.size.__qualname__.__len__() is 11 ('Struct.size': 'Struct.'=7 + 'size'=4)"]

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# type(struct.Struct.size).__name__.__eq__('getset_descriptor')
# type(struct.Struct.format).__name__.__eq__('getset_descriptor')
# struct.Struct.format.__qualname__.__len__()==13
# struct.Struct.__doc__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('str')
# struct.Struct.size.__objclass__.__name__.__eq__('Struct')
#
# Wave 271 theme: Both Struct.size and Struct.format are getset_descriptor; Struct.__doc__ is str.
#
# struct.Struct.size and struct.Struct.format are both getset_descriptor type
# (C-level data descriptors defined via PyGetSetDef). struct.Struct.format
# qualname is 'Struct.format' (13 chars: 'Struct.'=7 + 'format'=6 — 2 chars
# longer than size's 11 chars). struct.Struct.__doc__ is a str (the docstring
# for the Struct class). No prior struct spec anchors both size and format
# type names as __eq__() checks in a grouped table.
# Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

table struct_extra107.Struct_size_format_type_names_and_doc_type:
  description: "type(Struct.size).__name__.__eq__('getset_descriptor')==True / type(Struct.format).__name__.__eq__('getset_descriptor')==True / Struct.format.__qualname__.__len__()==13 / Struct.__doc__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('str')==True / Struct.size.__objclass__.__name__.__eq__('Struct')==True — size and format are both getset_descriptor (C-level PyGetSetDef descriptors in _struct.c); format qualname is 13 chars (2 more than size=11); Struct.__doc__ is str; __objclass__ is Struct; extra98 anchors class names; first structattr107 anchor"
  kind: python_call_eq
  category: descriptor_identity
  id_prefix: structattr107

  columns: [id, function, args, expected, description]
  rows:
    - [size_type_eq,     "Struct.size.__class__.__name__.__eq__",    ["getset_descriptor"], true, "type(Struct.size) is 'getset_descriptor' (C-level PyGetSetDef descriptor; reads compiled struct size in bytes)"]
    - [format_type_eq,   "Struct.format.__class__.__name__.__eq__",  ["getset_descriptor"], true, "type(Struct.format) is 'getset_descriptor' (C-level PyGetSetDef descriptor; reads the format string)"]
    - [format_qual_len,  "Struct.format.__qualname__.__len__",       [],                    13,   "Struct.format.__qualname__.__len__() is 13 ('Struct.format': 'Struct.'=7 + 'format'=6; 2 more than size=11)"]
    - [doc_type_str,     "Struct.__doc__.__class__.__name__.__eq__", ["str"],               true, "Struct.__doc__.__class__.__name__ is 'str' (Struct has a docstring; it is a Python str)"]
    - [size_objclass2,   "Struct.size.__objclass__.__name__.__eq__", ["Struct"],            true, "Struct.size.__objclass__.__name__ is 'Struct' (grouped again; confirms all getset_descriptors on Struct share same __objclass__)"]

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# struct.calcsize.__qualname__.__eq__('calcsize')
# struct.pack.__qualname__.__eq__('pack')
# struct.unpack.__qualname__.__eq__('unpack')
# struct.Struct.size.__qualname__.__eq__('Struct.size')
# struct.Struct.format.__qualname__.__eq__('Struct.format')
#
# Wave 271 theme: Module-level function qualnames vs Struct descriptor qualnames.
#
# struct.calcsize, struct.pack, struct.unpack are module-level C-level functions
# with qualnames 'calcsize', 'pack', 'unpack' (no class prefix). Struct.size
# and Struct.format are class-level descriptors with qualnames 'Struct.size'
# and 'Struct.format' (with 'Struct.' prefix). This contrast illustrates
# that class-level attributes include the class name in the qualname, while
# module-level functions have bare qualnames. struct_extra104 anchors module-
# level qualname equality; this spec groups them with descriptor qualnames.
# Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

table struct_extra107.module_function_qualnames_vs_descriptor_qualnames:
  description: "calcsize.__qualname__.__eq__('calcsize')==True / pack.__qualname__.__eq__('pack')==True / unpack.__qualname__.__eq__('unpack')==True / Struct.size.__qualname__.__eq__('Struct.size')==True / Struct.format.__qualname__.__eq__('Struct.format')==True — module-level functions have bare qualnames (no prefix); class-level descriptors have 'Struct.' prefix in qualname; contrast illustrates qualname prefix rules; extra104 anchors module-level equalities; first structattr107 anchor"
  kind: python_call_eq
  category: descriptor_identity
  id_prefix: structattr107

  columns: [id, function, args, expected, description]
  rows:
    - [calcsize_qualname, "calcsize.__qualname__.__eq__",         ["calcsize"],      true, "struct.calcsize.__qualname__ is 'calcsize' (no class prefix; module-level C function in _struct; 8 chars)"]
    - [pack_qualname,     "pack.__qualname__.__eq__",             ["pack"],          true, "struct.pack.__qualname__ is 'pack' (no class prefix; module-level C function in _struct; 4 chars)"]
    - [unpack_qualname,   "unpack.__qualname__.__eq__",           ["unpack"],        true, "struct.unpack.__qualname__ is 'unpack' (no class prefix; module-level C function in _struct; 6 chars)"]
    - [size_qualname3,    "Struct.size.__qualname__.__eq__",      ["Struct.size"],   true, "Struct.size.__qualname__ is 'Struct.size' (has 'Struct.' prefix; class-level getset_descriptor; 11 chars)"]
    - [format_qualname3,  "Struct.format.__qualname__.__eq__",    ["Struct.format"], true, "Struct.format.__qualname__ is 'Struct.format' (has 'Struct.' prefix; class-level getset_descriptor; 13 chars)"]

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# struct.Struct.size.__qualname__.__eq__('Struct.size') — standalone
#
# struct.Struct.size.__qualname__ is 'Struct.size' (11 chars: 'Struct.'=7 +
# 'size'=4). Struct.size is a getset_descriptor that returns the compiled
# size (in bytes) of the struct format string — this is the number of bytes
# that pack() will produce or unpack() expects. For example, Struct('!IH').size
# is 6 (4 bytes for unsigned int + 2 bytes for unsigned short). struct_extra98
# anchors Struct.size class name and qualname (as attribute access, not __eq__
# method call); struct_extra104 anchors __objclass__ for Struct.size; this spec
# anchors Struct.size qualname string equality via __eq__() as a standalone.
# Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

invariant struct_extra107.Struct_size_qualname_eq:
  description: "struct.Struct.size.__qualname__.__eq__('Struct.size') == True — qualname is 'Struct.size' (11 chars; 'Struct.'=7 + 'size'=4); getset_descriptor returning compiled struct size in bytes; __objclass__ is Struct; extra98 anchors qualname as attribute; extra104 anchors __objclass__; first standalone for Struct.size qualname __eq__ under structattr107"
  category: descriptor_identity
  kind: python_call_eq
  function: "Struct.size.__qualname__.__eq__"
  args: ["Struct.size"]
  expected: true

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# struct.Struct.format.__qualname__.__eq__('Struct.format') — standalone
#
# struct.Struct.format.__qualname__ is 'Struct.format' (13 chars: 'Struct.'=7 +
# 'format'=6). Struct.format is a getset_descriptor that returns the format
# string used to create the Struct instance. For example, Struct('!IH').format
# is '!IH'. The format string uses byte order prefixes (@, =, <, >, !, or none)
# followed by format characters (b, B, h, H, i, I, l, L, q, Q, f, d, s, p, P,
# x, etc.). The Struct.format qualname (13 chars) is 2 chars longer than
# Struct.size (11 chars) because 'format' (6 chars) is 2 chars longer than
# 'size' (4 chars). struct_extra98 anchors Struct.format qualname as attribute
# access; this spec anchors it as __eq__() method call standalone.
# Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

invariant struct_extra107.Struct_format_qualname_eq:
  description: "struct.Struct.format.__qualname__.__eq__('Struct.format') == True — qualname is 'Struct.format' (13 chars; 'Struct.'=7 + 'format'=6); getset_descriptor returning the format string used to create Struct; 2 chars longer than Struct.size (11); extra98 anchors qualname as attribute; extra104 anchors __objclass__; first standalone for Struct.format qualname __eq__ under structattr107"
  category: descriptor_identity
  kind: python_call_eq
  function: "Struct.format.__qualname__.__eq__"
  args: ["Struct.format"]
  expected: true

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# struct.Struct.size.__objclass__.__name__.__eq__('Struct') — standalone
#
# struct.Struct.size.__objclass__.__name__ is 'Struct'. The __objclass__
# attribute of a getset_descriptor is the class on which the descriptor is
# defined. For Struct.size, __objclass__ is the Struct class, whose __name__
# is 'Struct'. This confirms that size is a class-level descriptor defined
# directly on Struct, not on a base class or mixin. The Struct class is the
# only class in the _struct module that has size and format as getset_descriptors.
# struct_extra104 anchors Struct.size __objclass__ name equality; this spec
# anchors it as a standalone in the new structattr107 theme.
# Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

invariant struct_extra107.Struct_size_objclass_name_eq:
  description: "struct.Struct.size.__objclass__.__name__.__eq__('Struct') == True — __objclass__ is the class the descriptor is defined on; Struct.__name__ is 'Struct' (capital S; 6 chars); both size and format have __objclass__==Struct; confirms size is defined on Struct not a base class; extra104 anchors __objclass__ equality; first standalone under structattr107"
  category: descriptor_identity
  kind: python_call_eq
  function: "Struct.size.__objclass__.__name__.__eq__"
  args: ["Struct"]
  expected: true

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# type(struct.Struct.size).__name__.__eq__('getset_descriptor') — standalone
#
# type(struct.Struct.size).__name__ is 'getset_descriptor'. getset_descriptor
# is the type for C-level data descriptors defined via PyGetSetDef in CPython's
# C API. Struct.size is defined in Modules/_struct.c using PyGetSetDef to expose
# the compiled struct size as a read-only attribute. getset_descriptor is
# distinct from member_descriptor (used for simple C struct member access) and
# from property (used for Python-level descriptor protocol). Both Struct.size
# and Struct.format are getset_descriptor type. struct_extra98 anchors
# Struct.size __class__.__name__ attribute; this spec anchors type name via
# __eq__() as a standalone under structattr107.
# Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

invariant struct_extra107.Struct_size_type_is_getset_descriptor:
  description: "type(struct.Struct.size).__name__.__eq__('getset_descriptor') == True — Struct.size is a getset_descriptor (C-level PyGetSetDef data descriptor in _struct.c; read-only; exposes compiled struct size); distinct from member_descriptor (simple C struct member) and property (Python-level); both size and format are getset_descriptor; extra98 anchors class name; first standalone under structattr107"
  category: descriptor_identity
  kind: python_call_eq
  function: "Struct.size.__class__.__name__.__eq__"
  args: ["getset_descriptor"]
  expected: true

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# struct.Struct.format.__objclass__.__name__.__eq__('Struct') — standalone
#
# struct.Struct.format.__objclass__.__name__ is 'Struct'. Like Struct.size,
# Struct.format has __objclass__ equal to the Struct class. __objclass__ is
# 'Struct' (capital S, 6 chars). The Struct class name 'Struct' (capital S)
# distinguishes it from the struct module name 'struct' (lowercase s). The
# 'Struct.' prefix in the qualnames ('Struct.size', 'Struct.format') uses
# capital S, matching the class name. Both size and format share the same
# __objclass__ (Struct), confirming they are both defined on the same class.
# struct_extra104 anchors format __objclass__; this spec anchors it as
# a standalone under structattr107. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

invariant struct_extra107.Struct_format_objclass_name_eq:
  description: "struct.Struct.format.__objclass__.__name__.__eq__('Struct') == True — __objclass__ is Struct (capital S; 6 chars); both size and format share same __objclass__ Struct; 'Struct' (capital S class) vs 'struct' (lowercase module name); extra104 anchors format __objclass__; first standalone under structattr107"
  category: descriptor_identity
  kind: python_call_eq
  function: "Struct.format.__objclass__.__name__.__eq__"
  args: ["Struct"]
  expected: true
